§
Some definitions

¶ DEF:goodness
Goodness

A thing is good iff it is desirable.

¶ DEF
Stupidity

To think that [DEF:goodness] is useful.

§
Our main results

¶ THMS:main
Main

[]	ITM:1
	Nothing lasts forever.

[]	ITM:2
	All is well iff

	[]	ITM:2a
		nothing is bad, and

	[]	ITM:2b
		I know that '[ITM\:2+]' is rendered nicely, like this: [ITM:2+].

	[+]	ITM:2+
		I know that '[ITM\:2a]' is rendered nicely, like this: [ITM:2a].

[X]	ITM:X
	'[ITM\:2a]' -> [ITM:2a]

-	'[ITM\:2+]' -> [ITM:2+]

'[ITM\:2a]' -> [ITM:2a]

'[ITM\:2+]' -> [ITM:2+]

'[ITM\:1]' -> [ITM:1]

'[ITM\:X]' -> [ITM:X]


¶ PRF:main
of [THMS:main]

By straightforward induction on the complexity of nothing.

